    <h2>Group A: Attempt any two questions:(2 x 10 = 20)</h2><h3>Question 1</h3>
<div><p><p>What is S-D cut? For the following network flow find the maximal flow from S to D.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-5692  aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/scut-question-2075-min.jpg?resize=440%2C221&ssl=1" alt="What is S-D cut? For the following network flow find the maximal flow from S to D." width="440" height="221" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/scut-question-2075-min.jpg?w=1000&ssl=1 1000w, https://i0.wp.com/hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/scut-question-2075-min.jpg?resize=768%2C386&ssl=1 768w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 440px) 100vw, 440px" /></p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>A S-D cut of transparent network is edge whose removal will divide the network into two halves X and x̅ where</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Source vertext S ∈ X</li>
<li>Sink Vertex D ∈ X</li>
</ul>
<p>It is denoted by (X, Y)</p>
<p>Let&#8217;s find maximum flow from S to D using S-D cut method.</p>
<div class="table_wrapper" style="overflow-x:auto;"><table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 312px;">
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 24px;">
<td style="width: 25%; height: 24px;">X</td>
<td style="width: 25%; height: 24px;">Y</td>
